  "local_port": 37526,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I make clothes in Roblox?",
  "response": "Creating custom clothing for Roblox avatars is a fun way to personalize your in-game character or even create items to sell in the Roblox marketplace. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you design and upload your own clothes to Roblox:\n\n### **1. **Prerequisites**\n\n- **Roblox Account:** Ensure you have an active Roblox account. If you plan to sell clothing items, you'll need a [Premium](https://en.help.roblox.com/hc/en-us/articles/203313410-Roblox-Premium) membership.\n  \n- **Graphic Editing Software:** You'll need an image editor to design your clothing. Popular choices include:\n  - **Adobe Photoshop:** A professional-grade tool (paid).\n  - **GIMP:** A free, open-source alternative.\n  - **Paint.NET:** Another free option with user-friendly features.\n  \n- **Roblox Studio (Optional):** Useful for more advanced customization, but not required for basic clothing creation.\n\n### **2. **Understanding Roblox Clothing Templates**\n\nRoblox uses specific templates for different clothing items:\n\n- **Shirts and T-Shirts:** Use the shirt template.\n- **Pants:** Use the pants template.\n  \nYou can download official Roblox templates from the [Roblox Developer Hub](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/articles/Clothing-Templates).\n\n### **3. **Downloading the Templates**\n\n1. **Visit the Templates Page:**\n   - Go to the [Roblox Clothing Templates](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/articles/Clothing-Templates) page.\n\n2. **Download the Desired Template:**\n   - Choose between **Shirt Template** or **Pants Template** based on what you want to create.\n   - Save the template to your computer.\n\n### **4. **Designing Your Clothing**\n\n1. **Open the Template in Your Image Editor:**\n   - Use your chosen graphic editor to open the downloaded PNG template.\n\n2. **Understand the Layout:**\n   - The template has different sections labeled for various parts of the avatar (e.g., torso, arms, legs).\n   - Guides are usually provided to help you align your design correctly.\n\n3. **Create Your Design:**\n   - **Design Within Guidelines:** Ensure that your artwork stays within the designated areas to prevent overlapping or misaligned parts.\n   - **Use Layers:** If your software supports layers, use them to manage different parts of your design easily.\n   - **Transparency:** Keep the background transparent if it's not part of the clothing design.\n\n4. **Save Your Design:**\n   - Save your finished design as a PNG file to preserve transparency.\n\n### **5. **Uploading Your Clothing to Roblox**\n\n1. **Log In to Roblox:**\n   - Go to [Roblox](https://www.roblox.com/) and log in to your account.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Create Section:**\n   - Click on the **\"Create\"** button located at the top of the page.\n\n3. **Choose the Clothing Type:**\n   - Select **\"Shirts\"**, **\"Pants\"**, or **\"T-Shirts\"** based on what you created.\n\n4. **Upload Your Design:**\n   - Click on the **\"Choose File\"** button and select your designed PNG file.\n   - Enter a name for your clothing item.\n\n5. **Submit for Approval:**\n   - Click **\"Upload\"** to submit your clothing item.\n   - Note: If you have a Premium membership, your upload will be queued for approval.\n\n### **6. **Publishing and Using Your Clothing**\n\n- **Approval Process:**\n  - **Shirts and Pants:** Typically take a short time to review.\n  - **T-Shirts:** Usually get approved faster.\n\n- **Using Your Clothing:**\n  - Once approved, go to your **Avatar** settings.\n  - Navigate to the **Clothing** section and select your newly uploaded item to wear it.\n\n### **7. **Selling Your Clothing (Optional)**\n\nIf you have a Premium membership, you can sell your creations:\n\n1. **Set a Price:**\n   - When uploading your clothing, set a price in Robux.\n\n2. **Earnings:**\n   - You'll earn a percentage of the sales whenever another user purchases your item.\n\n3. **Promote Your Designs:**\n   - Share your creations within the Roblox community or on social media to increase visibility.\n\n### **8. **Tips for Successful Clothing Design**\n\n- **Stay Within Guidelines:** Adhere to [Roblox's Community Standards](https://en.help.roblox.com/hc/en-us/articles/203313410-Roblox-Premium) to ensure your designs aren't rejected.\n  \n- **Use High-Quality Images:** Clear and high-resolution designs look more professional and appealing.\n\n- **Be Creative:** Unique and original designs are more likely to stand out and be popular among players.\n\n- **Preview Your Design:** Use tools or features within Roblox Studio to preview how your clothing looks on different avatars before uploading.\n\n### **9. **Additional Resources**\n\n- **Roblox Developer Hub:** [Clothing Creation](https://developer.roblox.com/en-us/articles/Clothing-Creation)\n  \n- **Tutorial Videos:** Platforms like YouTube have numerous tutorials on designing and uploading Roblox clothing.\n  \n- **Community Forums:** Engage with other creators on the [DevForum](https://devforum.roblox.com/) for tips and feedback.\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps, you'll be able to create and customize clothing items for Roblox avatars effectively. Happy designing!",
